The paper deals with the problem of non-adaptive group testing, which involves identifying defective items from a set of items using a set of tests. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper's focus on constructing efficient nonrandom measurement matrices and decoding algorithms further supports these potential sub-categories.
